com.qtplaf.library.trading.data

Class PersistorDataList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qtplaf.library.trading.data.DataList
      • com.qtplaf.library.trading.data.PersistorDataList

  • public class PersistorDataList
extends DataList
    A data list that retrieves its data from persistor. The contract for a persistor of data lists is that fields must be defined as follows:
    • The first field is always the index, an auto-increment field starting preferably at 1, but not mandatory to start at 1, not negative and indexed.
    • The second field is a long, the time of the timed data.
    • All subsequent persistent fields are of type double and are considered data.
    With this structure, the PersistorDataList can handle not only Data data, but any timed Data.
    Author:
    Miquel Sas
